	<a name="106661672394253631">&nbsp;</a><br>
	<a href="http://news.com.com/2009-1001_3-1001340.html?tag=st_rn">Database dichotomy | CNET News.com</a>.&nbsp; This 2003-05-14 article accounts for the drive to reduce complexity while still needing brawny databases at the high end.&nbsp; Customers are demanding more reliable, easier to manage, and cheaper to maintain systems.  A Gartner analyst noticed more and more competition based on cost and manageability.&nbsp; The competition among DB2, Oracle, and SQL Server in mid-range installations is now bearing that out.<br>
